oc:kn_0a0c10c2 a oc:DesignPrinciple ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating new presentations without templates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "ALWAYS analyze content subject matter and match color palette, fonts, and visual elements to the topic, industry, mood, and target audience before creating slides" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Design alignment with content purpose creates professional, impactful presentations rather than generic, forgettable slides" .

oc:kn_6f7bb9fe a oc:Idempotency ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing iterative edits on existing presentations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The unpack-edit-pack workflow can be safely repeated multiple times - each iteration produces valid OOXML as long as validation passes after each edit" ;
    oc:hasRationale "The validation step ensures each edit cycle maintains schema compliance, enabling safe incremental modifications" .

oc:kn_8c78f30a a oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before creating or editing any presentation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Read the entire html2pptx.md or ooxml.md reference file COMPLETELY before starting any presentation work - NEVER set range limits when reading these files" ;
    oc:hasRationale "These files contain critical syntax rules, validation requirements, and anti-patterns that prevent file corruption and rendering failures" .

oc:kn_9c57f13a a oc:Constraint ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating HTML slides for conversion" ;
    oc:directiveContent "ALL text MUST be wrapped in <p>, <h1>-<h6>, <ul>, or <ol> tags - never use bare text in <div> or <span> elements as it will be silently ignored" ;
    oc:hasRationale "The html2pptx converter only processes text within proper semantic text elements" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_b76f7f43 a oc:AntiPattern ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When using html2pptx workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "NEVER use CSS gradients or custom fonts in HTML slides - always pre-rasterize gradients to PNG and use only web-safe fonts (Arial, Helvetica, Times New Roman, Georgia, Courier New, Verdana, Tahoma, Trebuchet MS, Impact)" ;
    oc:hasRationale "CSS gradients do not convert to PowerPoint and custom fonts cause rendering failures across different systems" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_b846a0b2 a oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When replacement text causes validation errors" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When text inventory validation fails, the replace.py script shows all errors at once with available shapes and actual overflow measurements - use these specific diagnostics to fix issues" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Batch validation prevents iterative trial-and-error and provides exact information needed to correct shape references and text overflow" .

oc:kn_bb69e58c a oc:Heuristic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing slide layouts with data visualizations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For slides with charts or tables, use two-column layout (header full-width + text in one column, featured content in other) or full-slide layout - NEVER vertically stack charts below text in single column" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Vertical stacking creates poor readability and layout issues; two-column or full-slide layouts optimize space and visual impact" .

oc:kn_bbc7b123 a oc:AntiPattern ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When adding charts, shapes, or text via PptxGenJS API" ;
    oc:directiveContent "NEVER use # prefix with hex colors in PptxGenJS code - use FF0000 not #FF0000 as the hash prefix causes file corruption" ;
    oc:hasRationale "PowerPoint's internal color format does not include the # prefix and including it corrupts the file structure" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_ce363040 a oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating presentations using existing templates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For template-based presentations: (1) Extract text and create thumbnails, (2) Analyze template structure, (3) Create outline with template mapping, (4) Rearrange slides, (5) Extract text inventory, (6) Generate replacements, (7) Apply and validate" ;
    oc:hasRationale "This systematic workflow ensures proper template utilization, prevents placeholder mismatches, and maintains design consistency" .

oc:kn_d2350686 a oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After editing XML and before packing the final presentation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before packing OOXML edits, always: clean unused resources, fix Content_Types.xml declarations, fix relationship IDs, remove broken references, and validate all slides/layouts/themes are properly declared" ;
    oc:hasRationale "OOXML requires strict schema compliance - orphaned resources or missing declarations create files that PowerPoint cannot open" .

